  • Method Details

    • insert

      public TNode<E> insert(E data)
      If element is not present in the tree, it inserts the element in the tree and splays it on to the top of the tree. If the element already exists in the tree, it will splay it on to the top and return that node.
      Specified by:
      insert in interface Tree<E extends Comparable<E>>
      Parameters:
      data - is the element to be inserted
      Returns:
      Returns the node of the tree if already present in the tree, else returns null.

    • insertNode

      public TNode<E> insertNode(TNode<E> node, TNode<E> newNode)
      Inserts the element in the tree, by recursively calling the function. Based on the value of the data to be added the right or the left subtree will be traversed accordingly.
      Parameters:
      node - is the tree where the element is to be inserted
      newNode - is the new element to be inserted into the tree
      Returns:
      Returns the root after the new node is inserted

    • search

    • searchNode

      public TNode<E> searchNode(TNode<E> node, E data)
      Searches the element in the tree, if element is found and if it is not the root node it will splay the element to the top of the tree by rotating the tree to the left or right based on its position.
      Parameters:
      data - is the element to be searched
      node - is the sub-tree to be searched(left or right sub-tree if it is not found in the root node)
      Returns:
      Returns the node of the tree if present in the tree, else returns null
